{% include "_letterhead.j2" %}

Re: Request for validation of debt
Original creditor: {{ collection.original_creditor or "(not yet disclosed)" }}
Alleged amount: ${{ "%.2f" % collection.alleged_amount }}
{% if collection.account_mask %}Original account ending: {{ collection.account_mask }}
{% endif %}{% if collection.first_contact_date %}First contact: {{ collection.first_contact_date }}
{% endif %}

To {{ collection.collector_name or "the collection agency" }},

This is a written request, made pursuant to 15 U.S.C. §1692g(b), for
validation of the debt referenced above. I do not waive any rights
under the FDCPA or FCRA. Until you have validated this debt in writing,
you must cease all collection activity.

Please provide all of the following:

  1. The name and address of the original creditor.
  2. Verification of the debt — copies of the original signed
     application or contract, statements showing how the alleged
     amount was calculated, and any assignment-of-debt or
     bill-of-sale documentation establishing your authority to
     collect.
  3. The date of last activity on the account and the date of first
     delinquency, as reported to consumer reporting agencies.
  4. Confirmation that the debt is within {{ collection.state or "my state" }}'s
     statute of limitations for collection.

I prefer to be contacted only in writing at the address above. Do not
contact me by telephone, at my workplace, or through any third party.

Sincerely,


{{ profile.name }}
